  "elapsed_s": 44.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She had some second cousins in Brussels.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was arranged that she would take the four oldest children-- not Reggie who was only 18 months old-- take us to the Belgian border.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there she and my cousin from Belgium would board the train and try and talk the conductor into letting us in.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So in December-- I'm getting on to the story-- in December, I'm not sure of the exact date, sometime before Christmas, before Hanukkah, my-- we all boarded the train in Cologne, Germany.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And my mother went with us to the border, which was Aachen, A-A-C-H-E-N.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then from Aachen, the train went by itself into the Belgian part of the border called [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And in [NON-ENGLISH], sure enough, my mother's cousin boarded the train and talked the conductor into letting us four children into Belgium.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's how we were able to get out.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
